e room assignments  mailbox numbers  email addresses  and Reserve Office Training Corps  ROTC  information  New cadets who did not attend the Summer Transition Program will be issued their athletic uniform at Matriculation  New cadets who attended the Summer Transition Program should bring all uniform items issued to them  New cadets whose last last name begins with  A L report to Cameron Hall 7 30 a m    9 00 a m  M Z report no later than 9 00   11 30 a m  to Cameron Hall Matriculation Day Schedule  Schedule subject to Change  7 30 a m    11 30 a m  Matriculation  Cameron Hall 8 00 a m  1 p m Matriculation Fair  Crozet Hall 2 00 p m  Superintendent s Welcome  Cameron Hall All new cadets must wear VMI issued athletic uniform to welcome ceremony    Approximately 2 30 p m  March Off  Cameron Hall 3 00 p m  Finish for the day VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 